      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That makes sense. You mentioned European or East Asian backgrounds, but I'm wondering about other regions. To be honest, we're looking to see if there's a natural fit for the brand in areas like Sub-Saharan Africa or Latin America, or if those markets just don't align with the \"sophisticated/refined\" image Patek and Rolex have built. In your professional opinion, do those demographics fit the \"ideal consumer\" profile for this level of luxury, or is the brand identity fundamentally tied to a more Western/Eurocentric standard of prestige?",
